## Context

- Performance is crucial for user experience and SEO
- Astro prioritizes server-side rendering for better performance
- Optimize Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, FID, TTI)

## Web Vitals

Optimize Core Web Vitals metrics:

### LCP (Largest Contentful Paint) - < 2.5s

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD - Optimize LCP
---

<!-- Load critical content first -->
<header class="bg-white">
  <h1>{criticalContent}</h1>
</header>

<!-- Optimized images -->
<Image 
  src="/hero.jpg" 
  alt="Hero" 
  width={1200} 
  height={600}
  loading="eager"
  format="webp"
/>

<!-- ❌ AVOID -->
<img src="/large-unoptimized.jpg" />
```

LCP Best Practices:
- Use Astro's `<Image>` with explicit dimensions
- Use WebP for images
- Preload critical resources with `<link rel="preload">`
- Minimize blocking JavaScript
- Use streaming SSR

### CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift) - < 0.1

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD - Avoid CLS
---

<!-- Explicit dimensions for images -->
<Image 
  src="/photo.jpg" 
  alt="Photo" 
  width={800} 
  height={600}
/>

<!-- Placeholders for dynamic content -->
<div class="min-h-[400px]">
  {asyncContent}
</div>

<!-- ❌ AVOID -->
<img src="/photo.jpg" />
<div>{asyncContent}</div> <!-- No fixed height -->
```

CLS Best Practices:
- Always specify `width` and `height` for images
- Use placeholders for async content
- Avoid inserting content above existing content
- Use `font-display: swap` for fonts

### FID (First Input Delay) - < 100ms

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD - Minimize FID
---

<!-- Minimize client JavaScript -->
<script>
  // Minimal and optimized code
  document.addEventListener('click', handleClick);
</script>

<!-- ❌ AVOID - Too much JavaScript -->
<script>
  // Load heavy libraries unnecessarily
  import heavyLibrary from 'heavy-library';
</script>
```

FID Best Practices:
- Minimize JavaScript sent to client
- Defer loading non-critical scripts
- Avoid long JavaScript tasks
- Use `client:idle` or `client:visible` instead of `client:load`

## Image Optimization

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD - Optimized images
---

<Image 
  src="/image.jpg" 
  alt="Description" 
  width={800} 
  height={600}
  format="webp"
  quality={80}
  loading="lazy"
  decoding="async"
/>

<!-- For critical images -->
<Image 
  src="/hero.jpg" 
  alt="Hero" 
  width={1200} 
  height={600}
  format="webp"
  loading="eager"
  fetchpriority="high"
/>
```

Best Practices:
- Use WebP with automatic fallback
- Always specify `width` and `height`
- Use `loading="lazy"` for non-critical images
- Use `loading="eager"` and `fetchpriority="high"` for LCP
- Adjust `quality` as needed (80 by default)

## Async Loading and Streaming

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD - Progressive loading
---

<!-- Critical content loaded immediately -->
<main>
  <h1>{title}</h1>
  {criticalContent}
</main>

<!-- Secondary content loaded after -->
<aside>
  <AsyncComponent />
</aside>

<!-- ❌ AVOID - Load everything in series -->
---
const data1 = await loadData1();
const data2 = await loadData2();
const data3 = await loadData3();
---
```

Best Practices:
- Load data in parallel with `Promise.all()`
- Use streaming SSR for progressive content
- Separate critical content from secondary content
- Use slots to organize loading

## JavaScript Optimization

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD - Minimal JavaScript
---

<!-- Inline scripts only if necessary -->
<script>
  // Minimal and optimized code
  const button = document.getElementById('btn');
  button?.addEventListener('click', handleClick);
</script>

<!-- ❌ AVOID -->
<script>
  // Import heavy libraries unnecessarily
  import _ from 'lodash';
  import moment from 'moment';
</script>
```

Best Practices:
- Minimize client JavaScript
- Use native browser APIs
- Avoid heavy dependencies if possible
- Use tree-shaking
- Defer non-critical scripts

## Cache and CDN

```astro
---
// Configuration in astro.config.mjs
---

// ✅ Use appropriate cache
export default defineConfig({
  // Static assets cache
  build: {
    assets: '_assets',
  },
  // Cache headers (if adapter supports it)
});
```

Best Practices:
- Use a CDN for static assets
- Configure appropriate cache headers
- Use browser cache (`Cache-Control`)
- Use Service Workers for offline cache if necessary

## DB Query Optimization

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD - Optimized queries
---

// Load in parallel
const [users, posts, comments] = await Promise.all([
  db.user.findMany({ take: 10 }),
  db.post.findMany({ take: 5 }),
  db.comment.findMany({ take: 20 }),
]);

// Avoid N+1 queries
const posts = await db.post.findMany({
  include: {
    author: true, // Load author in a single query
    comments: {
      take: 10,
    },
  },
});

// ❌ AVOID - N+1 queries
const posts = await db.post.findMany();
for (const post of posts) {
  const author = await db.user.findUnique({ where: { id: post.authorId } });
}
```

Best Practices:
- Use Prisma's `include` or `select` to avoid N+1
- Load data in parallel with `Promise.all()`
- Use `take` and `skip` for pagination
- Index frequently used columns in queries

